17 Sec. 5. The fact that an applicant:
18 (1) has faced charges of a crime described in section 4(5) or
19 4(6) of this chapter that were ultimately dismissed; or
20 (2) has been charged with a crime described in section 4(5) or
21 4(6) of this chapter, but not convicted of the crime;
22 is not sufficient grounds to disqualify the applicant for a license
23 under this article in the absence of other facts determined by the
24 commission to support a finding of unsuitability under section 4(9)
25 through 4(11) of this chapter.
26 Sec. 6. The costs of investigating an applicant for a license under
27 this chapter must be paid from the initial license fee paid by the
28 applicant under IC 4-39.5-13.
29 Sec. 7. The commission shall conduct or cause to be conducted
30 a background investigation of each applicant for a license issued
31 under this chapter.
32 Sec. 8. Criminal history record information obtained during the
33 investigation of an individual must be maintained by the
34 commission for the term of the license and for any subsequent
35 license term.
36 Sec. 9. The commission may require that an application or other
37 document submitted by an applicant or a licensee must be sworn
38 to or affirmed before a notary public.
39 Sec. 10. An applicant must furnish all information requested by
40 the commission, including financial data and documents,
41 certifications, consents, waivers, and individual histories.
42 Sec. 11. (a) An initial license issued under this chapter is valid
