6 Chapter 13. License Fees
7 Sec. 1. The commission shall charge the following initial license
8 fees:
9 (1) Twenty-five thousand dollars ($25,000) for an initial
10 manufacturer license, an initial distributor license, or an
11 initial supplier license issued to a person residing or domiciled
12 in Indiana.
13 (2) Thirty-five thousand dollars ($35,000) for an initial
14 manufacturer license, an initial distributor license, or an
15 initial supplier license issued to a person residing or domiciled
16 in a state other than Indiana or a country other than the
17 United States.
18 (3) Fifteen thousand dollars ($15,000) for an initial operator
19 license issued to a person residing or domiciled in Indiana.
20 (4) Twenty-five thousand dollars ($25,000) for an initial
21 operator license issued to a person residing or domiciled in a
22 state other than Indiana or a country other than the United
23 States.
24 (5) Five hundred dollars ($500) for an initial establishment
25 license.
26 Sec. 2. (a) A person holding a distributor license, a
27 manufacturer license, or a supplier license shall pay an annual
28 license renewal fee of ten thousand dollars ($10,000).
29 (b) A person holding an operator license shall pay an annual
30 license renewal fee of five thousand dollars ($5,000).
31 (c) The commission shall charge each person holding an
32 establishment license the following annual license renewal fees:
33 (1) One hundred dollars ($100) for a licensed establishment
34 that had adjusted gross receipts of less than twenty-five
35 thousand dollars ($25,000) in the previous twelve (12)
36 calendar months.
37 (2) Two hundred fifty dollars ($250) for a licensed
38 establishment that had adjusted gross receipts of at least
39 twenty-five thousand dollars ($25,000) but less than fifty
40 thousand dollars ($50,000) in the previous twelve (12)
41 calendar months.
42 (3) Five hundred dollars ($500) for a licensed establishment
2026 IN 1235—LS 6864/DI 125

27
1 that had adjusted gross receipts of at least fifty thousand
2 dollars ($50,000) but less than one hundred thousand dollars
3 ($100,000) in the previous twelve (12) calendar months.
4 (4) One thousand dollars ($1,000) for a licensed establishment
5 that had adjusted gross receipts of at least one hundred
6 thousand dollars ($100,000) in the previous twelve (12)
7 calendar months.
8 Sec. 3. A licensee shall pay the annual license renewal fee due
9 under section 2 of this chapter on the first day of the calendar
10 month containing the anniversary date of the issuance of the
11 licensee's establishment license.
12 Sec. 4. The commission shall deposit the following into the state
13 general fund:
14 (1) All fees collected under this chapter.
15 (2) All application fees received under IC 4-39.5-5.
