6 9-20-4 and IC 9-20-18); and any other tax or fee that the department is
7 required to collect or administer.
8 SECTION 5. IC 35-45-5-15.5 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA
9 CODE AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS
10 [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 15.5. This chapter does not apply
11 to video gaming authorized by IC 4-39.5.
12 SECTION 6. IC 35-52-4-36 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
13 AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY
14 1, 2026]: Sec. 36. IC 4-39.5-10-1 defines a crime concerning video
15 gaming.
16 SECTION 7. IC 35-52-4-37 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
17 AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY
18 1, 2026]: Sec. 37. IC 4-39.5-10-2 defines a crime concerning video
